fields.engineering_tactics:
(1) Define a strict JSON schema for the onboarding payload (TypeScript type, JSON Schema validator on client, OpenAPI on server). EXAMPLE PAYLOAD SCHEMA:
```json
{
  "version": "3.2.1",
  "flow_id": "onboarding_v3_magician_us",
  "experiment_variant": "control",
  "locale": "en-US",
  "archetype": "magician",
  "theme_tokens": {
    "font_heading": "Cabinet Grotesk",
    "font_body": "Söhne",
    "color_surface": "#F4EFE6",
    "color_ink": "#1A1816",
    "color_accent": "#E36B2C"
  },
  "steps": [
    {
      "id": "welcome",
      "kind": "hero",
      "props": {
        "headline": "What if the next 30 days felt different?",
        "subhead": "We'll show you in 90 seconds.",
        "cta_label": "Begin",
        "cta_event": "NEXT",
        "illustration_id": "hero_orb_v3"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "goal_picker",
      "kind": "single_select",
      "props": {
        "question": "What brought you here?",
        "options": [
          { "value": "weight_loss", "label": "Lose weight", "icon": "goal_weight" },
          { "value": "build_muscle", "label": "Build muscle", "icon": "goal_muscle" },
          { "value": "feel_better", "label": "Feel better", "icon": "goal_wellbeing" },
          { "value": "more_energy", "label": "More energy", "icon": "goal_energy" }
        ],
        "on_select_event": "ANSWER",
        "answer_key": "goal",
        "auto_advance_ms": 250
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "painpoint",
      "kind": "multi_select",
      "props": {
        "question": "What gets in the way?",
        "options": [
          { "value": "time", "label": "Time" },
          { "value": "motivation", "label": "Motivation" },
          { "value": "diet", "label": "Diet" },
          { "value": "sleep", "label": "Sleep" }
        ],
        "min": 1,
        "max": 3,
        "answer_key": "painpoints"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "loader",
      "kind": "theatrical_loader",
      "props": {
        "copy_stack": [
          "Analyzing your responses…",
          "Cross-referencing 2.4M users like you…",
          "Building your plan…"
        ],
        "min_duration_ms": 4000,
        "max_duration_ms": 7000,
        "on_complete_event": "PLAN_READY",
        "plan_endpoint": "/api/onboarding/plan"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "plan_reveal",
      "kind": "reveal",
      "props": {
        "headline_template": "Your {{archetype}} plan, {{user.name}}",
        "stitched_tokens": ["goal", "painpoints", "target_date"],
        "confetti_tier": "jackpot"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "paywall",
      "kind": "paywall_side_by_side",
      "props": {
        "plans": [
          { "sku": "weekly_3day_trial", "badge": "most_popular", "price": "$6.99/wk" },
          { "sku": "annual_50_off", "price": "$59.99/yr" }
        ],
        "cta_label": "Start free trial",
        "dismiss_event": "PAYWALL_DISMISSED"
      }
    }
  ],
  "transitions": {
    "welcome": { "NEXT": "goal_picker" },
    "goal_picker": { "ANSWER": "painpoint" },
    "painpoint": { "NEXT": "loader" },
    "loader": { "PLAN_READY": "plan_reveal" },
    "plan_reveal": { "NEXT": "paywall" },
    "paywall": { "PAYWALL_DISMISSED": "soft_paywall", "PAYWALL_PURCHASED": "completed" }
  }
}
```
(2) Client-side: a generic <OnboardingRenderer payload={config} /> that maps step.kind → pre-built native component (HeroScreen, SingleSelectScreen, etc.). Switch statement on kind, with fallback for unknown kinds. (3) Schema validation: validate every payload before render via Zod / ajv — reject invalid configs to a fallback default. (4) Versioning: payload includes version; client supports last 3 schema versions; new fields are additive only (no breaking changes). (5) Pre-fetch on app launch (parallel with splash): config endpoint should respond in <500ms; cache last-known-good config locally for offline / cold-start. (6) FSM (item 30) consumes the payload's transitions map to construct an XState machine at runtime. (7) Theme tokens in payload allow archetype/locale-driven visual variants without binary change. (8) Fallback: if config fetch fails, use bundled-in default config (offline robust). (9) Experiment routing: server returns config by user_id + experiment_variant assignment (PostHog/Eppo/Statsig); client never decides variant. (10) Telemetry: every step view/event reports config_version + experiment_variant + step_id back to analytics. (11) Component library MUST be production-grade — SDUI doesn't generate UI, it composes existing components. Build the catalog first (12-20 step kinds), THEN go server-driven. (12) Schema review process: payload schema is a contract; design + product + eng all approve schema changes. (13) Authoring tool: visual editor (Plotline / Adapty / custom) so non-engineers can ship config without dev cycle.
